reviews.review_text: Fun Show This was the first tape I ever received and I listened to it over and over. It's great to hear this excellent soundboard copy. Great performances and a quirky set list. Strange that they end a first set with China Rider! Good Times, Pocky Way and Samson are a fun way to start off the second set. This is what I would call a party show with lots of upbeat song choices. Special mentions go to a rare Race is On and a beautiful Black Muddy River to close the show (Jerry sounds a little tired but this is one tune where that actually sounds good).

fine show, interesting setlist but okay look thanks for putting this fileset together

and this is a good and interesting '89 show from the part of  the year where things started to build momentum. check out all the interesting placements, etc

but, and I know this is nitpicking, but seriously

why the hell do you break up playin' into two tracks when it's a standard version of  the song ?!?!?!?!?!?!

there's no logic to where that track edit is...that playin jam is a bit intense but very typical for the era in its style and sound...

it's really not a big deal and I know it's funny to be all WTF about it but seriously how the hell do you talk yourself into that being a separate track, that's just funny
